+# 🧪 Testing
+
+Unit tests cover the pure logic paths that don't require root privileges or a live network:
+
+```
+tests/
+├── test_classify.py     # web/SSH exposure classification (incl. regression test for the banner-vs-port fix)
+├── test_cve_lookup.py   # banner parsing, product/version extraction, OpenSSH version normalization
+├── test_engine.py       # TTL-based OS fingerprinting heuristic
+└── test_validator.py    # target validation (DNS resolution mocked)
+```
+
+Run with:
+
+```
+pip install pytest
+pytest tests/ -v
+```
+
+26 tests, all passing. Scanning/packet logic itself is exercised via manual integration testing against local test services (see Sample Output above) since it requires raw socket privileges.
